The paper deals with computer vision and deep neural networks, which are typically studied in the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of binary and ternary weights is a technique for reducing memory size and increasing processing speed, which is relevant to the neural networks (cs.NE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper proposes a new method for training neural networks, which falls under the deep learning (cs.DL) sub-category.
